microprocessor_definition.name: Ponys Microcontroller Tools - Antenna Triangulation
microprocessor_definition.description: calculates angle, distance and gps coordinates of a sending antenna

object.script:
function onTick() mapX = input.getNumber(1) mapY = input.getNumber(2) zoom = input.getNumber(3)
myGpsX = input.getNumber(4) myGpsY = input.getNumber(5)
senderGpsX = input.getNumber(6) senderGpsY = input.getNumber(7)
end
function onDraw() S = screen SW = S.getWidth() SH = S.getHeight()
-- sender position x,y = map.mapToScreen(mapX, mapY, zoom, SW, SH, senderGpsX, senderGpsY) S.setColor(0,0,120,180) S.drawCircleF(x,y, 2)
-- my position S.setColor(120,0,0,180) S.drawRectF(SW/2-2,SH/2-2, 3, 3) end

-- this script draws the underlying map and takes care of map controls -- the map position and zoom is forwared to the other lua script that draws custom information
zoom = 0.1 icWi = 7 scWi = 0 scHe = 0
tmp = false tmpX = 0 tmpY = 0
function onTick() remoteX = input.getNumber(1) remoteY = input.getNumber(2)
isC = input.getBool(3) cX = input.getNumber(3) cY = input.getNumber(4)
step = 5*zoom
if isC then if iPiR(cX, cY, 0, scHe/2-10, 10, 20) then doLeft = true if not tmp then doTmp() else tmpX = tmpX - step end elseif iPiR(cX, cY, scWi-10, scHe/2-10, 10, 20) then doRight = true if not tmp then doTmp() else tmpX = tmpX + step end elseif iPiR(cX, cY, scWi/2-10, 0, 20, 10) then doUp = true if not tmp then doTmp() else tmpY = tmpY + step end elseif iPiR(cX, cY, scWi/2-10, scHe-10, 20, 10) then doDown = true if not tmp then doTmp() else tmpY = tmpY - step end elseif iPiR(cX, cY, 0, 0, 11, 11) then if tmp then endTmp() end elseif iPiR(cX, cY, 0, scHe-10, 10, 10) then zoom = zoom - 0.05 elseif iPiR(cX, cY, 10, scHe-10, 10, 10) then zoom = zoom + 0.05 else stop() end else stop() end if zoom < 0.1 then zoom = 0.1 end if zoom > 50 then zoom = 50 end
if tmp then output.setNumber(1, tmpX) output.setNumber(2, tmpY) else output.setNumber(1, remoteX) output.setNumber(2, remoteY) end output.setNumber(3, zoom) end
F = false function stop() doLeft = F doRight = F doUp = F doDown = F end
function doTmp() tmp = true
tmpX = remoteX tmpY = remoteY end
function endTmp() tmp = false tmpX = 0 tmpY = 0 end
function onDraw() X = 0 Y = 0 if tmp then X = tmpX Y = tmpY else X = remoteX Y = remoteY end
screen.drawMap(X, Y, zoom)
if tmp then setClr(2, 138, 191) screen.drawRectF(0,0,10,10) setClr(255, 255, 255) screen.drawText(3,3,"X")
end
scHe = screen.getHeight() scWi = screen.getWidth()
if doLeft then setClr(2, 138, 191) else setClr(1, 69, 96) end screen.drawTriangleF(0, scHe/2, 6, scHe/2-6, 6, scHe/2+6)
if doRight then setClr(2, 138, 191) else setClr(1, 69, 96) end screen.drawTriangleF(scWi, scHe/2, scWi-6, scHe/2-6, scWi-6, scHe/2+6)
if doUp then setClr(2, 138, 191) else setClr(1, 69, 96) end screen.drawTriangleF(scWi/2, 0, scWi/2-6, 6, scWi/2+6, 6)
if doDown then setClr(2, 138, 191) else setClr(1, 69, 96) end screen.drawTriangleF(scWi/2, scHe, scWi/2-6, scHe-6, scWi/2+6, scHe-6)
screen.setColor(0,0,0,150) screen.drawRectF(0,scHe-10,20,10) setClr(2, 138, 191) screen.drawText(4,scHe-8,"+") screen.drawText(13,scHe-8,"-") end
function setClr(r,g,b) screen.setColor(r,g,b) end
function iPiR(x, y, reX, reY, reW, reH) return x > reX and y > reY and x < reX+reW and y < reY+reH end
